                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13984083" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 29 Apr 2014 07:10:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah we should likely use the factory to create an entity manager instance and use that, and then close it after use. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13984086" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 29 Apr 2014 07:17:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should apply for anything but the consumer (as the consumer is single threaded)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14108990" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2014 10:23:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a bit more tricky, as we would need to create the entity manager per exchange, and also deal with transactions for idempotent consumer / producer / consumer etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14140456" author="thelibrarian" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 13:22:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will this fix be backported to Camel 2.13.x ? 2.14.x dropped Java 1.6 support so we&apos;re currently stuck with 2.10 (as 2.11/2.12/2.13 are impacted)&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
